Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: Hi again,  Anyone who made a purchase would have had to register on the portal. We quickly put IP restrictions to prevent US individuals from purchasing as they are not allowed to participate, but a few got through or intentionally tried to work around the IP block.  If identified as from the US (after completing KYC) they would have been refunded in the USD value, but back to their funding method i.e. ETH, or BTC. If for some reason some participants have not submitted their KYC or contacted us at support@thinkcoin.io then we cannot help them until they do. Telegram and other forums are not support channels. For any further communication on this specific topic email support@thinkcoin.io.  Hope this clarifies your question.  Best regards, Caroline

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: Hi Exadro,  I understand your frustration, but we are doing this for the benefit of the project itself. Remember, ThinkCoin (TCO) is a utility token for the TradeConnect network and NOT a crypto currency to be used in other ecosystems or to be speculated on, there would be NO benefit to listing the token at this time just for the sake of listing. Our main project and achievement from the early beginning has been to be able to develop TradeConnect. ThinkCoin was our way of funding it - if you read our Whitepaper you would already be aware of this.  There's no reason to spread FUD about our ICO being a scam or that this will take a year, I do get that you have less hope in this as we have delayed the project for some time, but we are now strongly focusing on deliver on our exchange network that we know will make a difference to the current market and contribute to more efficient, transparent, cost-efficient trading on the blockchain.  Should you have any concerns - feel free to contact me directly on Telegram: @carolinethinkcoin or you can email support@thinkcoin.io.  Best regards, Caroline Marketing and Project Manager ThinkCoin

Author: Outsourced
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: Alot of exchanges have started last year even, hardly any get above $5m USD in volume a day, this token from appearance had said they had the product fully developed.  Untrue, they were also going to share 5% of their .2% trading fees let's break that down.  100,000,000 volume * .002 = $200,000 in fees if everyone shares the same fees (unlikely) * 5% = $10,000 divided amongst all of the sold out tokens....  10,000 / 500m, sorry that's incorrect they changed their total supply to make it look like it sold out.  10,000 / 21m = $.0004 per token held, which will decrease as bonus tokens get released.  So let's assume $ .00015 daily per token held, that's pretty good, then costs of sending that over drops it to $.0001 per day per token still pretty good except 100m volume must be achieved at a .2% trade fee rate.  In reality:  It'll look more like: 5m * .002 * .05  = 500 / 21m = .000002 USD per token held.

Body: We'd suggest you to read this :  Here is the official statement:  Hello everyone! I understand there is a lot of frustration at the moment, which I completely understand. We have decided to do a KYC for security and legal reasons to be certain we’re giving tokens to people who won’t abuse their privilege and to follow restrictions. We are aware this was not the plan from the beginning and we do apologise for any inconvenience. We will NOT be asking you to purchase any tokens and you will NOT have to provide with proof of residence. We hope to see your applications come through soon!

Author: Outsourced
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: I was interested until I realized: The roadmap is out of date The sale is apparelently permanent The telegram is full of bounty hunters and everyone is assumed to be a bounty Hunter No clear amount sold No distribution date  From July 11th the team said on here it was a successful funding round, apparelently not if private sales are still going.   Maybe this will be fixed in the future but right now this doesn't scream that there is a competent team running this project.

Author: MaZeeCM
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: Hi, thanks for your feedback! Let me answer this for you.   The roadmap is out of date ---> In which part of our Roadmap are you referring to? As far as we are concerned, we are on time with our roadmap. The roadmap is up to date, and can be viewed real-time on our Official Website: https://www.thinkcoin.io   The sale is apparelently permanent --->This has been answered already, it was announced, and currently, it's still on our pinned message on our Telegram Channel. This is why reading announcement is very important. There's a reason for it, let me copy and paste it for you. Here you go:   ❗️PUBLIC SALE IS OVER❗️  We have decided to take the remainder of the project into private sale after getting tremendous amount of interest from investors while traveling through 13 cities in all different continents. This means we are not holding a public token sale anymore. Should you want to participate please get in touch at: info@thinkcoin.io.  You can find out more about it here:  https://medium.com/thinkcointoken/an-important-thinkcoin-announcement-50a3b2f76906   The telegram is full of bounty hunters and everyone is assumed to be a bounty Hunter ---> This is NOT true. We treat everyone with respect. We have created a separate group for bounty hunters, to address all of their concerns there. So, it won't flood the main channel with questions about Bounty. You may join here, if you want to see it: https://t.me/ThinkCoin_Bounty   No clear amount sold ---> We did NOT continue on Public sale. It will be announced after we are done with the Token distribution. Please, stay tuned!  No distribution date ---> The first batch of minting will happen this weekend for all the private sale investors, after that, we will announce the distribution of tokens for bounty participants.   I hope I was able to answer all of your questions. We are not here to convince everyone how good the project is, or how good the people behind it. I suggest that you get yourself informed and well updated; from our Medium Blog: https://medium.com/thinkcointoken and Telegram Announcement Channel: https://t.me/ThinkCoin_Announcements   Best Regards,  MaZeeCM

Body: I Watch telegram, I've read a fair amount and to quote Carole today,  "Hi Everyone! We appreciate your patience and we understand you are all curious about where we stand and you all deserve to know, so early next week!! Don't miss it! 😄 Thanks again for your support and loyalty! Have a good weekend. Caroline"  "Distribution will be starting when sale is over and investors will be prioritised."   So you're starting distribution this weekend and continuing the sale privately?  Or no distribution this weekend because the sales running indefinitely?

Body: Introducing TCO Staking https://medium.com/thinkcointoken/introducing-tco-staking-26e492f69c25  TradeConnect’s development is well underway, and part of this process has been re-examining the platform to see how we can better reward our community and incentivise participation in the network.  With this in mind we are happy to announce a new feature in the network that will directly reward token holders, a feature we are calling Staking.  Holders who retain their ThinkCoin tokens long-term will receive a regular return from funds gathered using the Connect Fee. Five percent of the Connect Fee revenue allocated to the network itself (ie. 0.0125% of the total) will be held in a pool for stakers: the more the network grows, the greater our token holders are rewarded.  The dividends from the staking pool will be paid out at the end of every month, offering a regular return for our token holders.

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: Hello ThinkCoin Community!  We are proud to introduce you guys to a brand new feature in our network that will directly reward token holders. This will be called Staking. Read more about it in our Medium post and let us know should you have any questions:  https://medium.com/thinkcointoken/introducing-tco-staking-26e492f69c25

Author: DeViL303
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: We’ve landed in Seoul!    After attending a few events close to our home base, it’s time to kick start another Asian roadshow.  We have landed in Seoul for our first stop and in the center of Seoul at D. Camp. ThinkCoin and two other projects arranged an exclusive event to raise awareness about our project as a we’ve received a huge amount of interest from South Korea the last weeks.  Jacob Galea, our Head of Sales, gave a 30-minute presentation to a packed room of investors, interviewers and influencers from the area.  This week we have several meetings lined up before we will host another event this Saturday (June 23rd), also in Seoul. This will be an exclusive event on ThinkCoin alone, and we are very excited to connect with the people of Korea and get feedback on our project.  Not only will we be busy in Seoul, part of our team is also flying down to Singapore to attend the Blockchain for Finance Conference APAC in the Hilton Hotel on Wednesday 20th June and Thursday 21st June. https://medium.com/thinkcointoken/weve-landed-in-seoul-7416baed3300

Author: imyashir
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: Today we are proud to announce that we have officially joined forces with GMEX, one of the world’s leading exchange and blockchain service providers.  Our partnership with GMEX builds upon last month’s announcement that we would be working with decentralized cloud storage experts 0chain, and adds a major component to ThinkCoin and TradeConnect suite of solutions.  GMEX’s Fusion platform combines GMEX’s traditional centralised trading systems, which are currently live in multiple exchanges and post-trade venues, with the latest blockchain technology offering the best of both worlds for exchanges, clearing-houses and other institutions.  GMEX Fusion’s suite of capabilities will be combined with the TradeConnect multi-asset trading network, using ThinkCoin, the bespoke digital trading token unit of exchange.  GMEX Fusion will be integrated with TradeConnect’s mobile and web front ends. This will deliver options for both decentralised and centralised trading solutions, including CLOB and RFQ matching models, liquidity management, the ability to connect to third party crypto exchanges and a comprehensive set of market data options. The GMEX order execution API will be combined with TradeConnect’s matching model to create a sophisticated and agile trading solution representing the best of traditional centralised and blockchain-powered decentralised solutions.  A multi-asset blockchain-based exchange that will enable the trading of cryptocurrencies, equities, FX, commodities and more, TradeConnect will replace commissions with a levy on all trades that will be rebated to network participants in proportion to their participation. Traders will be connected with each other by an AI-powered scoring and matching model that will ensure the best trading conditions.  Pls read more.........

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: Good question, looking at competition is a crucial part of proper research before investing.  For our part, we don't agree entirely. While there are many other projects developing in this sector, almost all are focused around one financial product, whether it be forex, commodities or cryptocurrencies. TradeConenct is uniquely positioned to facilitate trade of a complete range of financial products - a service which we already have plenty of experience handling as part of the ThinkMarkets group.

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: It's a very good question! We think it can be answered by looking closely at the trading service we aim to provide. TradeConnect will facilitate trade between users, and the trustless blockchain system provides the structure to achieve this. Of course many exchanges exist that are positioned as authorities over their clients, at TradeConnect we are using the public ethereum blockchain to bring the benefits of transparency, immutability and security to our exchange. To gain the benefits of the blockchain the most effective model is to use a bespoke token for a project to power smart contracts on th ethereum network, and that's why TCO is an essential feature of the platform.  Does this answer your question?

Author: Makleyhill
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: ThinkCoin x GMEX  https://medium.com/thinkcointoken/thinkcoin-x-gmex-f1a46905d2b5  Today we are proud to announce that we have officially joined forces with GMEX, one of the world’s leading exchange and blockchain service providers.  Our partnership with GMEX builds upon last month’s announcement that we would be working decentralized cloud storage experts 0chain, and adds a major component to ThinkCoin and TradeConnect suite of solutions.  GMEX’s Fusion platform combines GMEX’s traditional centralised trading systems, which are currently live in multiple exchanges and post-trade venues, with the latest blockchain technology offering the best of both worlds for exchanges, clearing-houses and other institutions.  GMEX Fusion’s suite of capabilities will be combined with the TradeConnect multi-asset trading network, using ThinkCoin, the bespoke digital trading token unit of exchange.  GMEX Fusion will be integrated with TradeConnect’s mobile and web front ends. This will deliver options for both decentralised and centralised trading solutions, including CLOB and RFQ matching models, liquidity management, the ability to connect to third party crypto exchanges and a comprehensive set of market data options. The GMEX order execution API will be combined with TradeConnect’s matching model to create a sophisticated and agile trading solution representing the best of traditional centralised and blockchain-powered decentralised solutions.  A multi-asset blockchain-based exchange that will enable the trading of cryptocurrencies, equities, FX, commodities and more, TradeConnect will replace commissions with a levy on all trades that will be rebated to network participants in proportion to their participation. Traders will be connected with each other by an AI-powered scoring and matching model that will ensure the best trading conditions.  GMEX’s solution will be melded with the deep institutional experience and extensive IP of ThinkCoin’s platform and whitepaper. This combination will significantly enhance liquidity within the trading network’s ecosystem, enabling the network to achieve scale far faster than any other blockchain trading solution: factors that will together encourage uptake at a rate never before seen.  Here’s a word from our CEO and CO-founder, Nauman Anees:  “All of us at ThinkCoin are enormously excited to begin our collaboration with GMEX. The company’s culture of innovation and solution-oriented thinking is hugely impressive, and we look forward to together exploring the full potential of on and off-chain solutions to realise the promise of blockchain technology.”

Building on Ethereum goes beyond these practical reasons as well, because it allows us to be part of a wide community of dApp developers. We are able to connect with others working with the same tool kit and on the same infrastructure, facing the same obstacles. It allows us to collaborate and communicate easily with other projects, an invaluable asset in the new decentralized economy the blockchain will deliver."

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: This is the usual ICO model, if the soft cap is not meant, the project does not launch. For us, it would mean reconsidering our project. That might mean reexamining the budget we need to be successful, the marketing strategy we used (was our message not getting out to enough people?), and other factors. For example, maybe the the wider cryptocurrency ecosystem had an impact, with people losing faith in new projects following the 2018 crypto crash.  After examining all of these things we would come to the best conclusion and make a decision from there. We certainly won't be giving up on this project, that's for sure.

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: The benefit would likely be in the value of the tokens you are holding. As our platform grows there will be more demand for the tokens, but there will be a fixed supply, which would result in a price rise. Saying that, this is not a guarantee - TCO tokens are utility tokens.

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: Just a reminder the article is there.  To put it in really simple terms, having the entire trading platform on the blockchain isn't feasible with where Ethereum is currently at. In the future it may be possible though. Think of it like this, every trade needs two separate smart contracts, one for the offer, and one for the person matching (with both needing to be mined on the Ethereum network). Scaled up to tens of thousands of contracts, it's too much load.  The hybrid approach solves this. All finalized trades are recorded to the blockchain, giving the security and immutability. Before trades are finalized, the system uses an offline blockchain, which can handle almost limitless trades.  By combining off and onchain we can get the best out of both systems, overcoming the scalibility limitations of Ethereum currently. With plasma that will likely change, and we may be able to move our entire platform on to the live Ethereum network.  We hope this helps! Any questions, please feel free to ask!

Body: We are now accepting Credit Cards! https://medium.com/thinkcointoken/we-are-now-accepting-credit-cards-cb44599774a0    Credit cards now accepted for buying ThinkCoin Tokens  You asked for it, and we listened.  We are now officially accepting payments via credit card for ThinkCoin tokens. This allows you to buy directly in Sterling without having to pay any conversion fees.  Please note that only Mastercard transactions are currently accepted, with cards issued in Australia, Iraq, Israel, China, Canada, US and South Korea excluded.  Alternative payment methods include cryptocurrencies (Ethereum, Bitcoin & Bitcoin Cash), and wire transfer.  When do I get my tokens? Should you opt for a credit card, you will see your tokens in your balance after 120 days from the date of purchase.  This includes any early-bird bonus tokens you are eligible for.

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: The connect fee is not set in stone, and will be responsive to use of the platform in order for TradeConnect to be an attractive trading network. 25% of the Connect Fee will go to running the network, whilst the other 75% will go directly back to users of the platform.  The funds will be gathered into pools, one for makers (those who add orders to the orderbook and boost liquidity), who will receive 50%. The other pool is for takers, (those who take match orders already on the book and remove liquidity), who receive 25%. These pools will be sent out at the end of each day.  I hope this helps answer your question.

Body: If by rate you mean the value of TCO tokens, then no, actually the opposite! Once the network is operational, we expect many parties including both traditional brokers and individual traders to migrate some or all of their services to our network in order to take advantage of the Connect Fee. As the network usage grows, demand will sharply increase, and as no new tokens will enter the market we expect the price of tokens to increase.

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: That's always a possibility, but we think it will be unlikely as $2m has been raised in the first few days of the pre-ICO! We really believe in our project, and we're not about to just quit. If the soft cap isn't met we will likely take a step back to evaluate what went wrong. Perhaps we're not adequately getting across how promising we believe the project to be to the community, or possibly market-movements outside of our control are putting people off getting involved (the crypto crash). The likely scenario would be to make some changes and come back for another fundraising stage, but as I say, we think that will be unlikely.

Author: dustedlock
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: What's the advantage of a blockchain powered exchange versus a traditional exchange?

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: 1.Trading is not peer-to-peer, on a traditional exchange, creating credit and financial risk 2. A traditional exchange lacks transparency in price-making and trade execution. 3. Also, on traditional exchanges, settlement of trades and funds can take days, versus seconds on the blockchain. 4. A blockchain exchange solves the lack of flexibility in transferring trades.

Author: dzkrb
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: In white paper it is written. TradeConnect will break the market dominated by banks, primary brokers and large funds, creating a huge opportunity to become a leading multi-asset trading network to trade a wide range of financial products not found on traditional crypto-exchanges. Question. What financial products are we talking about?

Author: thinkcoin.io
Title: [ANN - ICO] ThinkCoin: Peer to Peer Multi Asset Trading on the Blockchain
Body: ThinkCoin is designed to allow trading in everyday financial products such as Stocks, Currencies (FX), Gold/Silver, Commodities, and also other Cryptocurrencies.
